query.name: query
query.description: Create a new query with an empty search query.

similarQuery.name: similarQuery
similarQuery.description:
Allows a search for similar objects, but the query has to be constructed on your end and included alongside an empty query.

The similarQuery should be made from the tags and keywords of the relevant object.

optionalFilters.name: optionalFilters
optionalFilters.description: Create filters for ranking purposes, where records that match the filter are ranked highest.
optionalFilters.type: string | readonly string[] | readonly (string | readonly string[])[]

schema.type: string | readonly string[] | readonly (string | readonly string[])[]

tagFilters.name: tagFilters
tagFilters.description:
Filter hits by tags. tagFilters is a different way of filtering, which relies on the _tags
attribute. It uses a simpler syntax than filters. You can use it when you want to do
simple filtering based on tags.

sumOrFiltersScores.name: sumOrFiltersScores
sumOrFiltersScores.description: Determines how to calculate the total score for filtering.

filters.name: filters
filters.description: Filter the query with numeric, facet and/or tag filters.

hitsPerPage.name: hitsPerPage
hitsPerPage.description: Set the number of hits per page.

offset.name: offset
offset.description: Specify the offset of the first hit to return.

length.name: length
length.description: Set the number of hits to retrieve (used only with offset).

attributesToSnippet.name: attributesToSnippet
attributesToSnippet.description: List of attributes to snippet, with an optional maximum number of words to snippet.

attributesToRetrieve.name: attributesToRetrieve
attributesToRetrieve.description: Gives control over which attributes to retrieve and which not to retrieve.

highlightPreTag.name: highlightPreTag
highlightPreTag.description: The HTML string to insert before the highlighted parts in all highlight and snippet results.

highlightPostTag.name: highlightPostTag
highlightPostTag.description: The HTML string to insert after the highlighted parts in all highlight and snippet results

snippetEllipsisText.name: snippetEllipsisText
snippetEllipsisText.description: String used as an ellipsis indicator when a snippet is truncated.

restrictHighlightAndSnippetArrays.name: restrictHighlightAndSnippetArrays
restrictHighlightAndSnippetArrays.description: Restrict highlighting and snippeting to items that matched the query.

maxValuesPerFacet.name: maxValuesPerFacet
maxValuesPerFacet.description: Maximum number of facet values to return for each facet during a regular search.

facetingAfterDistinct.name: facetingAfterDistinct
facetingAfterDistinct.description: Force faceting to be applied after de-duplication (via the Distinct setting).

minWordSizefor1Typo.name: minWordSizefor1Typo
minWordSizefor1Typo.description: Minimum number of characters a word in the query string must contain to accept matches with 1 typo

minWordSizefor2Typos.name: minWordSizefor2Typos
minWordSizefor2Typos.description: Minimum number of characters a word in the query string must contain to accept matches with 2 typos.

allowTyposOnNumericTokens.name: allowTyposOnNumericTokens
allowTyposOnNumericTokens.description: Whether to allow typos on numbers (“numeric tokens”) in the query string.

disableTypoToleranceOnAttributes.name: disableTypoToleranceOnAttributes
disableTypoToleranceOnAttributes.description: List of attributes on which you want to disable typo tolerance.

queryType.name: queryType
queryType.description: Controls if and how query words are interpreted as prefixes.

removeWordsIfNoResults.name: removeWordsIfNoResults
removeWordsIfNoResults.description: Selects a strategy to remove words from the query when it doesn’t match any hits.

advancedSyntaxFeatures.name: advancedSyntaxFeatures
advancedSyntaxFeatures.description: AdvancedSyntaxFeatures can be exactPhrase or excludeWords

optionalWords.name: optionalWords
optionalWords.description: A list of words that should be considered as optional when found in the query.

disableExactOnAttributes.name: disableExactOnAttributes
disableExactOnAttributes.description: List of attributes on which you want to disable the exact ranking criterion.

exactOnSingleWordQuery.name: exactOnSingleWordQuery
exactOnSingleWordQuery.description: Controls how the exact ranking criterion is computed when the query contains only one word.

alternativesAsExact.name: alternativesAsExact
alternativesAsExact.description: List of alternatives that should be considered an exact match by the exact ranking criterion.

enableRules.name: enableRules
enableRules.description: Whether rules should be globally enabled.

distinct.name: distinct
distinct.description: Enables de-duplication or grouping of results.

analytics.name: analytics
analytics.description: Whether the current query will be taken into account in the Analytics

analyticsTags.name: analyticsTags
analyticsTags.description: List of tags to apply to the query in the analytics.

synonyms.name: synonyms
synonyms.description: Whether to take into account an index’s synonyms for a particular search.

replaceSynonymsInHighlight.name: replaceSynonymsInHighlight
replaceSynonymsInHighlight.description: Whether to highlight and snippet the original word that matches the synonym or the synonym itself.

minProximity.name: minProximity
minProximity.description: Precision of the proximity ranking criterion.

responseFields.name: responseFields
responseFields.description: Choose which fields the response will contain. Applies to search and browse queries.

maxFacetHits.name: maxFacetHits
maxFacetHits.description: Maximum number of facet hits to return during a search for facet values.

percentileComputation.name: percentileComputation
percentileComputation.description: Whether to include or exclude a query from the processing-time percentile computation.

personalizationImpact.name: personalizationImpact
personalizationImpact.description:
The `personalizationImpact` parameter sets the percentage of the impact that personalization has on ranking records. The
value must be between 0 and 100 (inclusive). This parameter will not be taken into account if `enablePersonalization`
is **false**.

restrictSearchableAttributes.name: restrictSearchableAttributes
restrictSearchableAttributes.description: Restricts a given query to look in only a subset of your searchable attributes.

sortFacetValuesBy.name: sortFacetValuesBy
sortFacetValuesBy.description: Restricts a given query to look in only a subset of your searchable attributes.

typoTolerance.name: typoTolerance
typoTolerance.description: Controls whether typo tolerance is enabled and how it is applied.

aroundLatLng.name: aroundLatLng
aroundLatLng.description: Search for entries around a central geolocation, enabling a geo search within a circular area.

aroundLatLngViaIP.name: aroundLatLngViaIP
aroundLatLngViaIP.description: Search for entries around a given location automatically computed from the requester’s IP address.

aroundRadius.name: aroundRadius
aroundRadius.description: Search for entries around a given location automatically computed from the requester’s IP address.

aroundPrecision.name: aroundPrecision
aroundPrecision.description: Precision of geo search (in meters), to add grouping by geo location to the ranking formula.

insideBoundingBox.description: Search inside a rectangular area (in geo coordinates).

insidePolygon.description: Search inside a polygon (in geo coordinates).

ignorePlurals.description: Treats singular, plurals, and other forms of declensions as matching terms.

removeStopWords.name: removeStopWords
removeStopWords.description: Removes stop (common) words from the query before executing it.

naturalLanguages.name: naturalLanguages
naturalLanguages.description:
List of supported languages with their associated language ISO code.

Apply a set of natural language best practices such as ignorePlurals,
removeStopWords, removeWordsIfNoResults, analyticsTags and ruleContexts.

getRankingInfo.name: getRankingInfo
getRankingInfo.description: When true, each hit in the response contains an additional _rankingInfo object.

userToken.name: userToken
userToken.description:
A user identifier.
Format: alpha numeric string [a-zA-Z0-9_-]
Length: between 1 and 64 characters.

enableABTest.name: enableABTest
enableABTest.description:
Can be to enable or disable A/B tests at query time.
Engine's default: true

decompoundQuery.name: decompoundQuery
decompoundQuery.description:
Enable word segmentation (also called decompounding) at query time for
compatible languages. For example, this turns the Dutch query
"spaanplaatbehang" into "spaan plaat behang" to retrieve more relevant
results.

relevancyStrictness.name: relevancyStrictness
relevancyStrictness.description:
The relevancy threshold to apply to search in a virtual index [0-100]. A Bigger
value means fewer, but more relevant results, smaller value means more, but
less relevant results.

enableReRanking.name: enableReRanking
enableReRanking.description: Whether this search should use Dynamic Re-Ranking.

tags.name: link
tags.text:
https://www.algolia.com/doc/guides/algolia-ai/re-ranking/

Note: You need to turn on Dynamic Re-Ranking on your index for it to have an effect on
your search results. You can do this through the Re-Ranking page on the dashboard.
This parameter is only used to turn off Dynamic Re-Ranking (with false) at search time.
